Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge brought against me for shoplifting a dress worth approximately 2000 pounds. I acknowledge my involvement in this offense and take full responsibility for my actions.

I would like to express my sincere regret for my behavior. I understand that what I did was wrong and I am truly sorry for the harm and inconvenience I caused to the store and its staff.

At the time of the incident, I was an 18-year-old high school student. This experience has been a valuable lesson for me as a first-time offender. It has made me realize the gravity of my actions and how they can impact my future and the lives of those around me.

As I reflect on this incident, I am committed to learning from this mistake and becoming a responsible and law-abiding citizen. I understand the importance of integrity and the need to treat others with respect and honesty.

I genuinely and deeply regret my actions and the disappointment they have caused to my family, friends, and those who have placed their trust and belief in me. I assure you that I am dedicated to making the necessary changes in my life to ensure that I never repeat such behavior.

As a first-time offender, I request that the court consider my young age, lack of any previous criminal record, and my genuine desire to learn from this experience as mitigating factors in determining the appropriate punishment for my actions.

Thank you for your attention to my case.
